# Case Study: Applicant Recruitment & Technical Assessment Engine
**Role:** Senior Programmer / Systems Architect  
**Impact:** 80% Faster Application Processing | High-Quality IT Hires

## 📌 The Challenge
Scaling the IT and operations teams required a way to filter high-quality talent without manual grading. The organization needed a system to track applicants and objectively test their technical skills.

## 🛠️ My Architectural Approach
I built a specialized recruitment pipeline that prioritizes automated evaluation.

### Key Technical Implementations:
* **Hackathon-Style Assessment Engine:** Designed scenario-based coding exams and technical assessments specifically for programmer applicants.
* **Applicant Tracking System (ATS):** Built a centralized dashboard for HR to monitor the recruitment workflow from initial application to final evaluation.
* **Objective Grading Logic:** Automated the scoring of technical exams, ensuring only top-tier candidates moved to the interview stage.

## 🚀 Impact & Results
* **Processing Speed:** Boosted application processing efficiency by **80%**.
* **Talent Quality:** Significantly improved the quality of technical hires by implementing rigorous, automated vetting.
